          <Base:Description type="examine">
             A broad, woven wool tapestry that hangs horizontally.  Across the field, the tapestry depicts the tale of the Avoirdupois conversion to the religion of S'Allumer.  The bottom half of the scene shows a myriad of colorful blue, purple, violet and white tents with banners and standards displayed off the points.  Prominently, in the central foreground of the scene is a much larger tent of teal blue that displays a royal crest on it's topmost banner, flying above the blue Avoirdupois standard. Inside the tent, a noble equine garbed in gold-trimmed white armor kneels upon the ground, head bowed and plumed helm at his feet. Above him stands a statuesque vulpine maiden wearing voluminous purple robes. The maiden appears to be surrounded by a vividly glowing emerald green aura. About midway through the tapestry, a bright golden and pink hued sunrise spreads across the sky over the top of the tents. Skyward, subtly detailed in the clouds, is the vision of a slim equine cradling an infant foal to her bosom.
          </Base:Description>
